include ../part-header.pug
	.section.width-max-readable.m-auto
		h1 ðŸ¤– Autoresponders
	.section.width-max-readable.m-auto.m-b-3
		#autoresponder-list-container.box.p-l-1.p-r-1.p-b-1.m-b-1
			h3 Autoresponder list
			#autoresponder-list-loading-status Loading...
			#autoresponder-list-wrapper.list-wrapper
				ul#autoresponder-list
		#autoresponder-editor-container.box.p-l-1.p-r-1.p-b-1.m-b-1
			h3 Edit autoresponder
			p.
				Editing an autoresponder with a new id will create a new autoresponder.
				Editing an autoresponder with an existing id will update the current
				autoresponder.
			div.m-b-0p5
				label Autoresponder id
				input#autoresponder-id.w-100.input
			div.m-b-0p5
				label Default tag reason
				input#autoresponder-default-tag-reason.w-100.input
				div
					small.
						The tag reason is a tag name that is included when items from this
						autoresponder are added to the queue. It makes it possible to remove
						all related queue items when a subscriber unsubscribers from emails
						associated with a particular tag. It can be a good idea is to use a
						list tag, e.g. list-main, if this autoresponder is associated with
						a particular list.
			div
				label Autoresponder
				textarea#autoresponder-definition(style='display:none')
				#autoresponder-editor
					#mermaid-container
					#step-editor-container
						#step-editor.sticky.top-0p5
			.m-t-1
				#post-autoresponder-output
				button#post-autoresponder-button.button.main Create/update autoresponder
				<span> </span>
				button#clear-autoresponder-editor-button.button.secondary(style='display:none') Clear editor
